# Cursor Rules for Kenya ERP Merchant Frontend

## SDK Generation
- **NEVER edit files in `/lib/sdk` folder manually**
- Always generate SDK from backend using: `npm run build && npm run openapi:merchant`
- Run this command in the backend (kenya-fuel-api) directory after making API changes
- The SDK is auto-generated from OpenAPI spec and should not be manually modified

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Follow existing patterns for components and pages
- Use shadcn/ui components consistently
- Implement proper error handling and loading states

## API Integration
- Use the generated SDK services for all API calls
- Handle authentication with useAuth hook
- Show proper error messages and success notifications
- Implement proper loading states for better UX

## UI/UX Guidelines
- Follow the existing design patterns from other pages
- Use consistent badge colors and styling
- Implement proper responsive design
- Add proper accessibility attributes

## Color and Contrast Requirements
- **ALWAYS use color combinations with good contrast in both light and dark themes**
- For inactive/secondary badges: Use `variant="outline"` with custom classes for better contrast
- For status indicators: Ensure text is readable against background in all theme modes
- Test color combinations in both light and dark modes before implementation
- Prefer semantic color classes that adapt to theme (e.g., `text-muted-foreground`, `bg-muted`)
- Avoid hardcoded colors that may not work well in both themes 